04/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The southern city of Nafplio will host the 4th Conference on Security and Co-operation in the Mediterranean on Sunday (6 February).
Presidents and senior level representatives of 24 EU and Mediterranean states are expected to participate in the event.
The Palestinian territories will also participate as a full member for the first time.
The discussions will focus on the need for dialogue to resolve crises and for boosting co-operation among countries in the Mediterranean.
(MPA - 03/02/05)
